===Etymology===
[[File:Treatyofwaitangi.jpg|thumb|The “Waitangi sheet”, one of [[nine]] [[document#Noun|documents]] which [[make up]] the {{w|Treaty of Waitangi}} ''(sense 2.2)'', [[regard#Verb|regarded]] as the [[founding#Adjective|founding]] document of [[New Zealand]]. This sheet was the first to be [[sign#Verb|signed]] by the [[consul]] for the [[British#Adjective|British]] [[Crown]] and [[Māori]] [[chief#Noun|chiefs]] at [[Waitangi]] on 6 February 1840.]]

{{root|en|ine-pro|*dʰregʰ-}}
The {{glossary|noun}} is derived from {{inh|en|enm|trete}}, {{m|enm|trety|t=bargaining, negotiation; discussion; conference, meeting; entreaty, persuasion; agreement, contract, covenant; arrangement, settlement; agreement between two rulers, states, etc.; written work on a particular subject, treatise; subdivision of a written work, section}}{{nb...|(Late Middle English) trate, (Middle English) traite, traitee, traitie, traitye, traytee, traytte, trayttye, traytye, treatye, treetee, tretee, tretei, treti, tretie, tretty, tretye|otherforms=1}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=trētẹ̄|pos=''n.''(3)|noformat=1|id=MED46986}}</ref> from {{der|en|xno|treté}}, {{m|xno|traité}}, {{m|xno|treaté}}, and {{der|en|fro|traité}}, {{m|fro|traitié}}{{nb...|traieté, traitei|otherforms=1}} (modern {{cog|fr|traité|t=agreement between two rulers, states, etc.; treatise}}); {{m|fro||traité}} or {{m|fro||traitié}} is:<ref name="OED">{{R:OED Online|pos=n|id=205395|date=December 2021|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=n}}</ref>

* a noun use of the {{glossary|past}} {{glossary|participle}} of {{m|fro|traiter|t=to treat; to deal with, handle}}, from {{der|en|la|tractāre}}, the {{glossary|present}} {{glossary|active}} {{glossary|infinitive}} of {{m|la|tractō|t=to drag, haul, tug; to handle, manage; to debate, discuss; to exercise, practise; to perform, transact}}, from {{m|la|trahō|t=to drag, pull}} (probably ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*tregʰ-|t=to drag, pull (?)}}, a variant of {{m|ine-pro|*dʰregʰ-|t=to drag, pull; to run}}) + {{m|la|-tō|pos={{glossary|frequentative}} {{glossary|suffix}}}}; and
* also from {{der|en|la|tractātum|t=written work on a particular subject, treatise}}, from {{der|en|la|tractātus|t=dragged, hauled, tugged; handled, managed; exercised, practised; performed, transacted}}, the {{glossary|perfect}} {{glossary|passive}} {{glossary|participle}} of {{m|la|tractō}} (see above).

