# {{lb|en|countable|international law}} A [[formal]] [[binding#Adjective|binding]] [[agreement]] [[conclude]]d by [[subject#Noun|subjects]] of [[international law]], namely, [[state#Noun|states]] and [[international#Adjective|international]] [[organizations]]; a [[convention]], a [[pact#Noun|pact]].
#: {{usex|en|to sign a peace '''treaty'''}}
#: {{usex|en|to write up a '''treaty''' touching climate change}}
#* {{RQ:Bacon Henry 7|page=47|passage=[T]he ''Duke of Britaine'' hauing beene an ''Hoſte'', and a kind of ''Parent'' or ''Foſter-father'' to the King, in his tenderneſſe of age, and vveakneſſe of fortune, did looke for at this time from King {{smallcaps|Henry}} (the renovvned King of ''England'') rather braue ''Troupes'' for his Succours, then a vaine '''''Treatie''''' of Peace.}}
#* {{RQ:Burnet History|volume=I|page=15|passage=Soon after his &#91;{{w|James VI and I}}'s&#93; coming to the Crown of ''England'' he entered into ſecret '''treaties''' with ''Spain'', in order to the forcing the States to a peace: {{...}}}}
#* {{RQ:Adam Smith Wealth of Nations|volume=II|chapter=Of the Principle of the Commercial, or Mercantile System|page=29|passage=Exportation was encouraged ſometimes by dravvbacks, ſometimes by bounties, ſometimes by advantageous '''treaties''' of commerce with foreign ſtates, and ſometimes by eſtabliſhment of colonies in diſtant countries.}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}}
## {{lb|en|uncountable}} ''Chiefly in'' '''in treaty''': [[discussion]]s or [[negotiation]]s in order to [[reach#Verb|reach]] an [[agreement]].
##* {{RQ:Evelyn Diary|volume=I|entrydate=30 April 1680|page=519|passage=To a meeting of the executors of late Visc{{sup|sse}} Mordaunt's estate, to consider of the sale of Parsons Greene; being in '''treaty''' with Mr. Loftus, and to settle the halfe yeare's account.}}
